| **`__post_init__`** | New — initializes `self._fds: dict[str, int]` to track per-project open file descriptors |
| **`acquire()`** | Re-entrant check via `project in self._fds`; PID compat gate for old-style locks; kernel-enforced `fcntl.flock(LOCK_EX \| LOCK_NB)` with `BlockingIOError` and `OSError` fallbacks; PID-file fallback when fcntl unavailable |
| **`release()`** | `_fds` is authoritative (`pop(project, None)` → no-op if never acquired); unlink-before-unlock prevents unlock→unlink TOCTOU; `fd == -1` sentinel for fallback PID path |
| **`is_locked()`** | Hybrid: flock probe on test fd → return `True` if `BlockingIOError` → PID fallback for old-style locks |

